sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Updates deposit balance of a financial account existing on a service provider.

Inputs :

  • Account Number - The value that identifies an account record.
  • Account Type - The value that categorizes the account ID
  • Amount - Amount value.
  • Remarks - Description for the transaction.

Outputs :

  • Transaction Details - Object containing these information about transaction :
    • Transaction Receipt ID - The identifier attached to a customer.
    • Status - Status of the transaction.
    • Sequence Number - Sequence Number of the transaction.
  • Action Status-An object with the following fields:
    • Code - If the request is executed successfully, code will be set to 0 but if the request failed, code will be set to 1.
    • Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages :

  • Amount should be greater than 0.

To use this action, the corresponding Jack Henry Associates jXchange Spoke Connection must be created and associated with the JHA Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

To use this action, the corresponding Jack Henry Associates jXchange Spoke SOAP Security Profiles must be created and associated with the JHA SOAP Security Policies. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use.
